00:16:11.490 --> 00:16:16.890
So most of us are more familiar with
Lamarck's second law here. This idea that

00:16:17.070 --> 00:16:22.160
adaptations made by an organism in
response to its environment get inherited

00:16:22.340 --> 00:16:26.790
by its offspring, right? So the sons of
the blacksmith must have bigger biceps, or

00:16:26.970 --> 00:16:30.050
the daughter of the giraffe gets a
slightly longer neck than her mother

00:16:30.230 --> 00:16:37.720
started with. But Lamarck also had this
first law that much as we developed from

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:43.100
simple cells to complex systems that all
organisms have a natural drive to

00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:48.550
complexify. These are great ideas but they
don't work out, right? They don't work out

00:16:48.730 --> 00:16:52.720
because now we know that reproductions
doesn't work that way. You don't just pass

00:16:52.900 --> 00:17:00.060
them the useful stuff or the more complex
stuff, or the exercise parts. What we've

00:17:00.240 --> 00:17:04.280
learned from Darwin, and since Darwin is
that we have to pay attention to

00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:09.310
reproduction and selection processes,
right? Organisms send along everything,

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:13.190
they send out everything, not just the
useful stuff, but they do it with their

00:17:13.370 --> 00:17:17.690
ability and noise. So the environment is
what's determining what will survive,

00:17:17.870 --> 00:17:23.050
right? So now we really have
two evolutionary processes on really,

00:17:23.230 --> 00:17:28.050
really different time scale. So we've got
human reproduction and selection on one

00:17:28.230 --> 00:17:32.570
hand, and language reproduction and
selection on the other. It's not that one

00:17:32.750 --> 00:17:38.130
recapitulates the other, it's each of them
is evolving in a shape by the processes of

00:17:38.310 --> 00:17:42.880
reproduction and selection. In human
reproduction we pass on what kind of

00:17:43.060 --> 00:17:48.280
patterns we can learn and it may be very
slowly and very long ago that more

00:17:48.460 --> 00:17:53.780
effective and more powerful pattern
